<The Second Category>

175
00:13:03,392 --> 00:13:04,710
No way...

176
00:13:07,269 --> 00:13:09,616
Yes!!

177
00:13:15,803 --> 00:13:17,105
Did I get that right?

178
00:13:17,105 --> 00:13:21,792
And finally, we have Maekawa Sonoko-san Vuru High.

179
00:13:22,345 --> 00:13:25,203
These five participants will go on to the next round.

180
00:13:25,203 --> 00:13:27,502
Will everyone please give these 5 a round of applause.

181
00:13:28,319 --> 00:13:29,859
Sanjyo Sakurako has been eliminated.

182
00:13:29,859 --> 00:13:33,378
As she is now, how can she even win?

183
00:13:33,945 --> 00:13:35,876
But I didn't expect Makino to qualify,

184
00:13:35,876 --> 00:13:37,388
even though she was mainly depending on luck.

185
00:13:37,388 --> 00:13:40,153
The next category tests one's knowledge and proficiency

186
00:13:40,153 --> 00:13:42,756
of English in a speech.

187
00:13:42,756 --> 00:13:46,768
The speech is titled "Unfortunate Children".

188
00:13:46,768 --> 00:13:49,822
"Unfortunate Children"?

189
00:13:49,822 --> 00:13:53,778
Before we begin, each contestant is given 15 minutes to prepare.

190
00:14:12,992 --> 00:14:17,170
Makino-san, you really look good,

191
00:14:17,170 --> 00:14:18,645
in the way you wore those clothes.

192
00:14:18,645 --> 00:14:20,069
Thanks.

193
00:14:20,618 --> 00:14:24,329
I really admire your creativity and spontaneity.

194
00:14:25,850 --> 00:14:32,542
However, I flew thousands of miles to get here,
so as to win this competition.

195
00:14:32,529 --> 00:14:35,131
I'm Tsukasa's fiance anyway.

196
00:14:35,799 --> 00:14:40,493
If Tsukasa really loves you as much as they say he does,

197
00:14:40,493 --> 00:14:43,180
then all the more I cannot lose to you.

198
00:14:43,913 --> 00:14:46,688
Let us fight this out fair and square.

199
00:15:04,444 --> 00:15:05,691
Tsukushi-chan.

200
00:15:07,852 --> 00:15:09,430
Sakurako.

201
00:15:09,430 --> 00:15:11,757
You're writing your draft in Japanese.

202
00:15:12,326 --> 00:15:15,555
Mm. I'll translate it to English once I'm done.

203
00:15:15,555 --> 00:15:17,311
Let me help you.

204
00:15:19,369 --> 00:15:22,417
Don't forget that I've been overseas for a long period of time.

205
00:15:27,564 --> 00:15:32,625
It seems that Domyoji-san's mom recommended
Kurimaki Ayano for this competition.

206
00:15:35,238 --> 00:15:37,220
So it seems.

207
00:15:38,158 --> 00:15:40,377
But, she really is very pretty.

208
00:15:40,377 --> 00:15:45,074
No wonder Domyoji's mom likes her.

209
00:15:45,074 --> 00:15:46,462
Tsukushi-chan.

210
00:15:47,253 --> 00:15:49,488
You definitely must win.

211
00:15:50,207 --> 00:15:52,785
I'm honestly supporting you.

212
00:15:52,785 --> 00:15:54,723
Sakurako.

213
00:15:55,645 --> 00:15:58,501
I'd have no chance at all if I had to contest with Kurimaki Ayano.

214
00:15:59,878 --> 00:16:04,292
I'll be doomed if she really wins and together with Domyoji...

215
00:16:04,304 --> 00:16:09,417
But if you win, then maybe there's still some chance left for me.

216
00:16:20,598 --> 00:16:22,206
<The Third Category>

217
00:16:22,206 --> 00:16:25,335
Next, the third round is about to begin.

218
00:16:25,335 --> 00:16:31,075
At the same time,
there are more unfortunate children in the world.

219
00:16:31,075 --> 00:16:37,187
Iraqi and Afghan losing their parents and home...

220
00:16:37,187 --> 00:16:40,529
That's really good. Her English is so fluent.

221
00:16:40,529 --> 00:16:43,453
Well, she is studying in London after all.

222
00:16:43,453 --> 00:16:45,989
Ah... I say...

223
00:16:50,245 --> 00:16:53,888
Everyone's so good. I wonder how Tsukushi will fair.

224
00:16:55,316 --> 00:16:59,082
Finally, we have Makino Tsukushi-san up on stage...

225
00:17:08,279 --> 00:17:16,901
Now, I am living in my father's company's residence
with my family.

226
00:17:16,901 --> 00:17:24,917
But, we have to leave it soon for his business reasons.

227
00:17:26,682 --> 00:17:29,958
Sis is actually talking about her personal life.

228
00:17:29,963 --> 00:17:33,356
Isn't the title "Unfortunate Children"?

229
00:17:38,329 --> 00:17:41,623
Even without a house to live in,

230
00:17:42,977 --> 00:17:49,750
I love my father, my mother, and my brother.

231
00:17:49,738 --> 00:17:56,750
The most important thing for me, is my family.

232
00:17:57,164 --> 00:17:58,839
What is she saying?

233
00:17:58,839 --> 00:18:00,461
I don't know.

234
00:18:01,203 --> 00:18:04,043
Not bad, Makino.

235
00:18:05,105 --> 00:18:12,183
I believe, what is most needed for deprived children,

236
00:18:12,183 --> 00:18:17,739
is... a warm family.

237
00:18:21,288 --> 00:18:29,417
And next, we will have the Main TOJ Judge announce the two finalists.

238
00:18:29,400 --> 00:18:33,990
The first finalist is the one with international experience and taste,

239
00:18:33,990 --> 00:18:36,922
Kurimaki Ayano-san.

240
00:18:38,688 --> 00:18:43,714
Kurimaki-san's perceptiveness is really spectacular.

241
00:18:44,799 --> 00:18:50,083
Next, we have discussed about this for quite some time...

242
00:18:50,066 --> 00:18:52,640
I have a suggestion here.

243
00:18:52,640 --> 00:18:56,043
What do you think if we pick the last finalist
by a game of scissors, paper, stone?

244
00:18:56,043 --> 00:18:56,841
What on earth?

245
00:18:56,841 --> 00:19:03,625
Let's see which beauty does the Goddess of Luck
have her eyes upon.

246
00:19:09,320 --> 00:19:14,345
Scissors, paper, stone!

247
00:19:18,442 --> 00:19:21,137
The result is...

248
00:19:21,137 --> 00:19:23,881
Makino Tsukushi-san!

249
00:19:24,216 --> 00:19:25,507
Yes!

250
00:19:26,417 --> 00:19:29,729
She did it!

251
00:19:30,806 --> 00:19:32,379
I've won!

252
00:19:38,441 --> 00:19:41,155
Hey hey, this isn't fair!

253
00:19:41,155 --> 00:19:43,117
That's right! What kind of joke are the judges trying to crack?

254
00:19:43,117 --> 00:19:45,237
The others' speech are all better than hers.

255
00:19:45,237 --> 00:19:46,485
Yea! That's right!

256
00:19:48,508 --> 00:19:51,575
The results of the earlier round were also ridiculous.

257
00:19:51,575 --> 00:19:54,845
You guys are just playing with the results!

258
00:19:57,916 --> 00:20:00,774
All of you, shut the hell up!

259
00:20:06,013 --> 00:20:09,535
This is a competition to pick the best girl.

260
00:20:10,180 --> 00:20:12,368
Ordinary people should just shut up.

261
00:20:13,370 --> 00:20:15,002
Domyoji.

262
00:20:15,890 --> 00:20:19,740
Makino! You can do this!

263
00:20:19,740 --> 00:20:22,519
I'll always be here watching you.

264
00:20:36,706 --> 00:20:39,031
Where were you?

265
00:20:39,031 --> 00:20:40,426
I was watching from here.

266
00:20:40,426 --> 00:20:41,882
Just felt a bit nervous.

267
00:20:47,845 --> 00:20:52,682
Next, the two finalists will be battling it out on stage.

268
00:20:54,642 --> 00:20:55,786
Tsukasa.

269
00:20:57,541 --> 00:21:00,428
What will you do if Ayano wins instead?

270
00:21:04,811 --> 00:21:06,857
I believe that Makino can do it.

271
00:21:13,618 --> 00:21:17,667
Next... The final category is homemaking.

272
00:21:17,649 --> 00:21:22,717
I would now like to invite the judges
who are specially for this round up on stage.

273
00:21:26,774 --> 00:21:28,088
What is this?

274
00:21:34,604 --> 00:21:40,625
The two finalists must now play with these 21 children
for the next 30 minutes.

275
00:21:40,612 --> 00:21:43,655
They may use any of the provided equipment.

276
00:21:43,655 --> 00:21:48,750
And finally, these kids will choose the person
whom they think is more fun to play with.

277
00:21:49,221 --> 00:21:52,340
Hello, everyone.

278
00:21:52,340 --> 00:21:54,165
Hello.

279
00:21:54,165 --> 00:21:56,501
Yup. Now follow me.

280
00:21:56,501 --> 00:21:58,288
Okay!

281
00:21:58,288 --> 00:21:59,223
Oh no.

282
00:21:59,223 --> 00:22:01,249
She took the first opportunity.

283
00:22:02,228 --> 00:22:07,083
He-ll-o, everyone!

284
00:22:07,071 --> 00:22:08,953
What's that for?

285
00:22:08,953 --> 00:22:10,747
She's just like an fool!

286
00:22:13,204 --> 00:22:15,156
Let's go, everyone.

287
00:22:15,156 --> 00:22:17,249
Yes.

288
00:22:17,249 --> 00:22:18,469
How outrageous...

289
00:22:18,469 --> 00:22:19,890
Looks like she took a big blow.

290
00:22:19,890 --> 00:22:21,446
The kids should know best.

291
00:22:21,446 --> 00:22:26,542
Everything that is happening in the room
is being broadcasted on the screen.

292
00:22:27,029 --> 00:22:29,492
What the hell are you doing, Makino?!

293
00:22:30,584 --> 00:22:32,885
Don't think so much. Just do what you need to do.

294
00:22:38,720 --> 00:22:42,947
Running with the wind...

295
00:22:42,947 --> 00:22:47,338
Dancing in the snow...

296
00:22:47,338 --> 00:22:51,837
Smiling at the snow.

297
00:22:51,837 --> 00:22:56,208
Oh no... This is really bad.

298
00:22:59,375 --> 00:23:01,690
I heard that you're just a poor commoner.

299
00:23:01,690 --> 00:23:02,263
Hah?

300
00:23:02,263 --> 00:23:04,833
What can you do, you bunch of poor people?

301
00:23:04,850 --> 00:23:06,712
Maybe you're just useless.

302
00:23:06,712 --> 00:23:09,366
This is just like F4...

303
00:23:09,993 --> 00:23:11,038
How old are you guys?

304
00:23:11,038 --> 00:23:12,977
Seven!

305
00:23:12,977 --> 00:23:16,306
Well, I'm 17, ya?

306
00:23:16,306 --> 00:23:17,936
Just like an old woman.

307
00:23:17,936 --> 00:23:20,917
What's there to be proud of, you poor person?

308
00:23:20,927 --> 00:23:22,533
Stupid!

309
00:23:23,191 --> 00:23:24,879
You...

310
00:23:27,419 --> 00:23:29,682
I get the feeling that Ayano is controlling this whole thing.

311
00:23:29,682 --> 00:23:32,906
You lads haven't earnt a cent for your ownselves.

312
00:23:32,906 --> 00:23:35,243
So go to h*ll.

313
00:23:36,088 --> 00:23:38,737
I wonder where I've heard that before...

314
00:23:43,832 --> 00:23:45,591
Let's go over there to play.

315
00:23:46,340 --> 00:23:51,615
Anyway, you guys don't play anything
other than TV games at home.

316
00:23:51,615 --> 00:23:55,879
What would you guys know how to play anyway?

317
00:24:02,567 --> 00:24:05,306
She's good. Very good.

318
00:24:05,942 --> 00:24:08,727
I can do that.

319
00:24:08,727 --> 00:24:10,954
Show me then.

320
00:24:27,099 --> 00:24:29,577
You don't even know how to play this properly.

321
00:24:30,995 --> 00:24:34,767
Kids will always be kids.

322
00:24:41,343 --> 00:24:43,683
Don't tell me she doesn't know that there are cameras in the room.

323
00:24:43,683 --> 00:24:44,633
Ya...

324
00:24:46,209 --> 00:24:47,979
Come on! Catch me!

325
00:25:12,078 --> 00:25:12,915
Alright...

326
00:25:24,970 --> 00:25:29,314
You old woman, never would have guessed...

327
00:25:30,211 --> 00:25:34,537
You lads, you're not bad yourselves...

328
00:25:34,537 --> 00:25:36,230
That looks like fun.

329
00:25:36,230 --> 00:25:38,538
Me too!

330
00:25:42,749 --> 00:25:43,940
Wait...

331
00:25:44,942 --> 00:25:47,310
Let's play! Let's play!

332
00:25:50,235 --> 00:25:53,232
Yea yea I got it.

333
00:25:57,229 --> 00:26:00,077
Tsukushi, what will we play next?

334
00:26:00,322 --> 00:26:03,051
Wait. Hang on a sec...

335
00:26:04,990 --> 00:26:06,211
Come on!

336
00:26:07,417 --> 00:26:09,203
Hey, Ayano-san.

337
00:26:09,203 --> 00:26:10,045
Huh?

338
00:26:11,227 --> 00:26:13,191
Come and help me will you?

339
00:26:13,191 --> 00:26:15,789
I can't handle all these kids alone.

340
00:26:15,789 --> 00:26:17,850
Mm.

341
00:26:18,600 --> 00:26:19,881
The two of them are playing together.

342
00:26:19,881 --> 00:26:20,705
1...

343
00:26:20,705 --> 00:26:21,867
2...

344
00:26:21,867 --> 00:26:23,152
3...

345
00:26:23,152 --> 00:26:24,296
4...

346
00:26:24,296 --> 00:26:28,524
Only you can do that, Makino.

347
00:26:28,524 --> 00:26:32,125
Whee... Ah... You tripped... Let's do it again.

348
00:26:34,605 --> 00:26:39,958
Ladies and gentlemen, all of the rounds
have finally been completed.

349
00:26:40,405 --> 00:26:46,792
Next, we will announce Teen Of Japan 2005's winner!

350
00:26:52,665 --> 00:26:57,129
Excuse me, judges...

351
00:26:57,651 --> 00:27:00,716
which sister did you like playing with more?

352
00:27:01,274 --> 00:27:06,235
On my count of three, you will run to the side
of the person of your choice.

353
00:27:09,581 --> 00:27:10,763
1...

354
00:27:15,564 --> 00:27:17,072
2...

355
00:27:18,830 --> 00:27:20,937
3...!

356
00:27:27,433 --> 00:27:30,697
Eh? What's wrong with everyone?

357
00:27:30,697 --> 00:27:34,684
Alright, now please run over to
whoever you found the most fun.

358
00:27:34,684 --> 00:27:35,631
I like both!

359
00:27:35,631 --> 00:27:38,869
So do I... Me too...

360
00:27:38,869 --> 00:27:40,911
I can't just choose one.

361
00:27:40,911 --> 00:27:44,607
Hey hey... This could be... Perhaps... Maybe...

362
00:27:44,607 --> 00:27:46,251
This is a first...

363
00:27:46,251 --> 00:27:49,744
Main Judge, what shall we do?

364
00:27:55,767 --> 00:28:03,833
Everyone, we have decided to use the results
of the entire competition to determine the winner.

365
00:28:03,837 --> 00:28:05,999
It's quite difficult to tell if you use the overall results...

366
00:28:05,999 --> 00:28:08,295
Nah, everything has already been decided.

367
00:28:08,295 --> 00:28:11,009
Just who will win?

368
00:28:11,009 --> 00:28:14,643
Only God knows...

369
00:28:26,081 --> 00:28:27,856
I apologise for making everyone wait.

370
00:28:27,856 --> 00:28:30,279
Announcing tonights lucky winner...

371
00:28:31,570 --> 00:28:40,792
The grand winner of Teen Of Japan 2005 is...

372
00:28:46,212 --> 00:28:49,334
Kurimaki Ayano-san.

373
00:28:54,713 --> 00:28:56,102
I lost.

374
00:29:07,659 --> 00:29:09,007
Congratulations.

375
00:29:09,007 --> 00:29:10,590
Thank you.

376
00:29:11,598 --> 00:29:16,875
Although the grand trophy has been
awarded to Kurimaki Ayano-san,

377
00:29:16,874 --> 00:29:21,993
our little judges have decided that there is no one winner.

378
00:29:22,801 --> 00:29:32,167
Hence, we will be awarding Makino Tsukushi-san
a special prize sum of 1 million yen.

379
00:29:32,147 --> 00:29:33,820
Eh?

380
00:29:45,468 --> 00:29:48,673
You've done well, Makino Tsukushi.

381
00:29:52,505 --> 00:29:54,931
We'll always be behind you, Tsukushi-chan.

382
00:29:54,931 --> 00:29:57,846
Tsukushi, you're the best!
You've changed my opinion of you.

383
00:30:11,673 --> 00:31:00,592
Tsukushi... Tsukushi... Tsukushi...

384
00:31:00,871 --> 00:31:07,000
Ma'am, Kurimaki Ayano-san has won the competition.

385
00:31:07,889 --> 00:31:09,401
That would be obvious.

386
00:31:09,401 --> 00:31:11,118
Makino, you've done very well.

387
00:31:11,118 --> 00:31:12,985
You're great, you got second!

388
00:31:12,985 --> 00:31:14,052
Congratulations.

389
00:31:14,052 --> 00:31:19,167
But, being second isn't enough to change anything.

390
00:31:19,153 --> 00:31:20,921
Who said so?

391
00:31:20,921 --> 00:31:21,305
Eh?

392
00:31:21,753 --> 00:31:24,620
What's going to happen later-
think about it later.

393
00:31:24,620 --> 00:31:27,638
Tomorrow will have tomorrow's troubles.

394
00:31:27,638 --> 00:31:31,101
We will always help you anytime you need it.

395
00:31:33,027 --> 00:31:33,910
Great!

396
00:31:33,910 --> 00:31:37,916
Let me organise a party today to celebrate
Makino winning second place.

397
00:31:37,916 --> 00:31:40,471
Let us, F4, settle this great party.

398
00:31:41,864 --> 00:31:43,829
Where's Domyoji?

399
00:31:43,829 --> 00:31:47,887
Ah, I saw him over there just now.

400
00:31:47,887 --> 00:31:49,272
Tsukushi!

401
00:31:49,272 --> 00:31:52,074
You're the best, Tsukushi!

402
00:31:52,074 --> 00:31:53,262
Mama is really touched.

403
00:31:53,262 --> 00:31:55,014
Onee-chan, you were very cool.

404
00:31:55,014 --> 00:31:56,923
You were great.

405
00:31:57,294 --> 00:32:00,391
I'm sorry, everyone. I couldn't win this.

406
00:32:00,391 --> 00:32:02,032
What are you saying?

407
00:32:03,007 --> 00:32:06,184
Tsukushi, you are my greatest daughter.

408
00:32:06,543 --> 00:32:08,568
You're the pride of Papa.

409
00:32:17,343 --> 00:32:21,250
Congratulations on winning in the end, Ayano-san.

410
00:32:21,250 --> 00:32:23,133
Thank you.

411
00:32:23,133 --> 00:32:27,853
From today onwards, I hope you'll take good care of Tsukasa.

412
00:32:27,853 --> 00:32:29,042
Ma'am?

413
00:32:29,043 --> 00:32:30,422
Yes?

414
00:32:30,982 --> 00:32:34,871
I think the one taking care of Tsukusa,

415
00:32:34,871 --> 00:32:37,243
should be Makino-san.

416
00:32:37,243 --> 00:32:38,600
You're kidding.

417
00:32:38,600 --> 00:32:41,382
Why do you say the same thing as they do?

418
00:32:41,382 --> 00:32:44,379
Although in the end I won,

419
00:32:44,379 --> 00:32:48,884
I think Makino-san has moved the hearts of many even more.

420
00:32:52,044 --> 00:32:59,375
I now fully understand the real reason
why Tsukasa loves Makino-san.

421
00:33:00,795 --> 00:33:07,333
Right now, I don't think I have any right to be Tsukasa's fiance.

422
00:33:31,694 --> 00:33:34,660
Makino! Congratulations to you!

423
00:33:50,821 --> 00:33:52,636
Where's Domyoji?

424
00:33:52,636 --> 00:33:55,741
He had something to do.

425
00:33:55,741 --> 00:33:57,882
I see.

426
00:34:11,981 --> 00:34:13,732
Mom.

427
00:34:17,047 --> 00:34:19,726
A deal is a deal.

428
00:34:21,686 --> 00:34:27,125
I know.
Seems like we just couldn't make it with our own power.

429
00:34:28,572 --> 00:34:31,823
But after seeing Tsukushi's performance,

430
00:34:32,468 --> 00:34:37,125
I've come to realise that one can only
touch others' hearts with one's own.

431
00:34:48,551 --> 00:34:51,950
Well then, take care, Mom.

432
00:34:58,713 --> 00:35:01,630
We're really very sorry.

433
00:35:03,019 --> 00:35:06,789
So it was you guys who cut up my clothes after all.

434
00:35:06,789 --> 00:35:11,042
But in the end, you really moved us deeply.

435
00:35:11,038 --> 00:35:12,682
Our tears were streaming out.

436
00:35:12,682 --> 00:35:16,176
I really felt that we did something wrong.

437
00:35:19,255 --> 00:35:27,500
Anyway, it was thanks to you cutting up my clothes
that I was able to attain second place.

438
00:35:30,041 --> 00:35:32,642
That's right!

439
00:35:33,290 --> 00:35:36,995
Well, we feel a lot better now.

440
00:35:42,852 --> 00:35:44,636
Hey hey...

441
00:35:58,897 --> 00:36:00,966
But you actually helped Tsukushi write her speech.

442
00:36:00,966 --> 00:36:03,136
That totally changed my impression of you.

443
00:36:03,136 --> 00:36:06,456
Then will you go out with me?

444
00:36:06,456 --> 00:36:07,345
No no he can't.

445
00:36:07,345 --> 00:36:09,213
Akira already has the old Lady Boss.

446
00:36:09,213 --> 00:36:10,872
Eh?

447
00:36:11,308 --> 00:36:13,453
You two really have a relationship going on?

448
00:36:13,453 --> 00:36:16,224
Ah, no it's not true... Just that...

449
00:36:17,115 --> 00:36:19,998
I cannot forget the men I've met before.

450
00:36:19,998 --> 00:36:29,458
But after seeing Tsukushi, I realise that I
should just stick to the one I truly like.

451
00:36:31,882 --> 00:36:34,112
At least now you know she's married. You're lucky, Akira.

452
00:36:34,112 --> 00:36:36,397
Then, you're single now right?

453
00:36:36,397 --> 00:36:39,410
How bout it?

454
00:36:40,614 --> 00:36:43,162
Uhh alright. I'll go out with you tomorrow.

455
00:36:44,328 --> 00:36:46,558
Nishikado-san, are you free tomorrow?

456
00:36:46,558 --> 00:36:48,787
I have a tea ceremony to attend. I'm very busy.

457
00:36:48,787 --> 00:36:52,046
Then if you have some spare time, will you let me know?

458
00:36:52,046 --> 00:36:54,334
Uh yea. I'll let you know if I have some free time.

459
00:36:54,334 --> 00:36:57,388
Really?!

460
00:36:57,388 --> 00:37:00,660
You must definitely let me know when you're free.

461
00:37:56,338 --> 00:37:59,285
You're slow, Domyoji.

462
00:38:15,264 --> 00:38:19,259
Umm, I...

463
00:38:21,076 --> 00:38:24,431
didn't win.

464
00:38:24,431 --> 00:38:26,673
I was watching.

465
00:38:28,203 --> 00:38:30,470
I'm truly sorry.

466
00:38:30,988 --> 00:38:34,465
And you were cheering me on all the way...

467
00:38:34,465 --> 00:38:38,708
Yep, I believe that you are a fine woman.

468
00:38:42,000 --> 00:38:44,963
Well then, about tomorrow...

469
00:38:48,246 --> 00:38:50,358
I'd like you to accompany for a while.

470
00:38:51,102 --> 00:38:51,952
Eh?

471
00:38:52,468 --> 00:38:59,083
I've already gotten ready 4 million yen. So let me settle it as 
Makino Tsukushi's Christmas gift.

472
00:38:59,098 --> 00:39:00,764
What are you saying?

473
00:39:00,764 --> 00:39:03,635
And that, 
together with the prize money from winning second place,

474
00:39:03,635 --> 00:39:05,802
adds up to about 5 million.

475
00:39:05,802 --> 00:39:07,615
You can't... That's too much...

476
00:39:07,615 --> 00:39:12,333
I've already returned your father his job.

477
00:39:12,328 --> 00:39:13,740
You're not kidding?

478
00:39:13,740 --> 00:39:15,530
Really.

479
00:39:16,178 --> 00:39:19,303
I'm going to be very busy.

480
00:39:19,857 --> 00:39:25,469
I've got a lot of things to do today, so I can't meet you.

481
00:39:27,132 --> 00:39:30,075
But then, it's still too much...

482
00:39:30,075 --> 00:39:34,292
So I say, go out with me tomorrow, alright?

483
00:39:35,066 --> 00:39:36,222
Mm.

484
00:39:38,252 --> 00:39:40,763
But, are you sure that much is fine?

485
00:39:40,763 --> 00:39:42,651
It's fine!

486
00:39:42,651 --> 00:39:48,333
Meet me at the food centre at 2 o'clock tomorrow.

487
00:39:50,968 --> 00:39:52,343
Got it.

488
00:39:54,563 --> 00:39:55,813
See you then.

489
00:39:58,526 --> 00:39:59,781
See you.

490
00:40:02,398 --> 00:40:03,775
Makino?

491
00:40:04,590 --> 00:40:05,934
Hmm?

492
00:40:07,341 --> 00:40:09,658
If today's competition was held again,

493
00:40:09,658 --> 00:40:12,520
you'll definitely be first.

494
00:40:14,063 --> 00:40:15,890
Thanks.

495
00:40:35,085 --> 00:40:36,484
Tsukushi.

496
00:40:37,336 --> 00:40:41,583
Just now, Lady Boss called and said that they've return
everything they took from the Confectionary shop.

497
00:40:41,566 --> 00:40:42,667
No kidding.

498
00:40:42,668 --> 00:40:43,667
It's true.

499
00:40:46,984 --> 00:40:49,150
That's great!

500
00:40:49,150 --> 00:40:52,333
Great! Let's toast to her achievement!

501
00:40:55,881 --> 00:40:57,318
Cheers...

502
00:40:57,318 --> 00:41:00,098
Cheers!

503
00:41:00,098 --> 00:41:04,551
Live long! Live long!

504
00:41:04,551 --> 00:41:06,064
Live Long!

505
00:41:06,064 --> 00:41:08,849
I was suddenly called back by my manager.

506
00:41:08,849 --> 00:41:09,902
Eh?

507
00:41:11,554 --> 00:41:14,961
You should have come to see me
personally about your job position.

508
00:41:15,766 --> 00:41:18,587
I've prepared a position for you as Section Manager.

509
00:41:19,385 --> 00:41:21,645
You're being promoted 2 levels,

510
00:41:21,645 --> 00:41:24,531
so come back and work here.

511
00:41:26,629 --> 00:41:28,231
You're the best Papa.

512
00:41:28,231 --> 00:41:31,114
The company really needs Papa after all.

513
00:41:31,114 --> 00:41:34,476
Today I specially made roasted chicken skin.

514
00:41:35,765 --> 00:41:38,710
Tsukushi got second place!

515
00:41:38,710 --> 00:41:39,940
Let's celebrate!

516
00:41:39,940 --> 00:41:41,448
Thank you for the food!

517
00:41:41,448 --> 00:41:43,533
Thank you for the food!

518
00:41:53,339 --> 00:41:54,558
Tsukasa.

519
00:41:54,558 --> 00:41:55,743
Oh, Rui.

520
00:41:56,262 --> 00:41:59,781
I was planning on meeting you when
I finished packing my stuff.

521
00:42:02,084 --> 00:42:04,206
Why didn't you attend the party?

522
00:42:05,430 --> 00:42:08,166
I had a lot of things to settle.

523
00:42:08,166 --> 00:42:09,538
I see.

524
00:42:09,538 --> 00:42:15,042
Hey Rui, can I trust you to do something important?

525
00:42:15,043 --> 00:42:16,242
Hmm?

526
00:42:17,509 --> 00:42:24,250
I'm asking you to do this,
because I believe you are a true man.

527
00:42:24,259 --> 00:42:26,071
What is it? Why?

528
00:42:26,071 --> 00:42:27,867
Well sit first Rui.

529
00:42:27,867 --> 00:42:29,973
